{"name":"Mathlib.Init.Function","instances":[],"imports":["Init"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L136-L137","name":"Function.RightInverse.id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.RightInverse.id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L133-L134","name":"Function.LeftInverse.id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.LeftInverse.id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L130-L131","name":"Function.uncurry_curry","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.uncurry_curry","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L127-L128","name":"Function.curry_uncurry","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.curry_uncurry","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L124-L125","name":"Function.uncurry","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.uncurry","doc":"Interpret a function with two arguments as a function on `α × β` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L120-L121","name":"Function.curry","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.curry","doc":"Interpret a function on `α × β` as a function with two arguments. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L111-L111","name":"Function.bijective_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.bijective_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L109-L109","name":"Function.surjective_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.surjective_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L107-L107","name":"Function.injective_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.injective_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L101-L105","name":"Function.LeftInverse_of_surjective_of_RightInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.LeftInverse_of_surjective_of_RightInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L98-L99","name":"Function.has_RightInverse.surjective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.has_RightInverse.surjective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L95-L96","name":"Function.RightInverse.surjective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.RightInverse.surjective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L90-L93","name":"Function.RightInverse_of_injective_of_LeftInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.RightInverse_of_injective_of_LeftInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L87-L88","name":"Function.has_LeftInverse.injective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.has_LeftInverse.injective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L84-L85","name":"Function.LeftInverse.injective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.LeftInverse.injective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L82-L82","name":"Function.has_RightInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.has_RightInverse","doc":"`has_RightInverse f` means that `f` has an unspecified right inverse. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L79-L79","name":"Function.RightInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.RightInverse","doc":"`RightInverse g f` means that g is a right inverse to f. That is, `f ∘ g = id`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L76-L76","name":"Function.has_LeftInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.has_LeftInverse","doc":"`has_LeftInverse f` means that `f` has an unspecified left inverse. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L73-L73","name":"Function.LeftInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.LeftInverse","doc":"`LeftInverse g f` means that g is a left inverse to f. That is, `g ∘ f = id`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L69-L70","name":"Function.bijective.comp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.bijective.comp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L67-L67","name":"Function.bijective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.bijective","doc":"A function is called bijective if it is both injective and surjective. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L61-L64","name":"Function.surjective.comp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.surjective.comp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L59-L59","name":"Function.surjective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.surjective","doc":"A function `f : α → β` is calles surjective if every `b : β` is equal to `f a`\nfor some `a : α`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L53-L55","name":"Function.injective.comp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.injective.comp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L51-L51","name":"Function.injective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.injective","doc":"A function `f : α → β` is called injective if `f x = f y` implies `x = y`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L48-L48","name":"Function.comp_const_right","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.comp_const_right","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L46-L46","name":"Function.comp.right_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.comp.right_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L44-L44","name":"Function.comp.left_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.comp.left_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L42-L42","name":"Function.comp.assoc","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.comp.assoc","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L40-L40","name":"Function.right_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.right_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L38-L38","name":"Function.left_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.left_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L35-L36","name":"Function.app","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.app","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L32-L33","name":"Function.swap","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.swap","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L28-L30","name":"Function.combine","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.combine","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L25-L26","name":"Function.on_fun","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.on_fun","doc":"Given functions `f : β → β → φ` and `g : α → β`, produce a function `α → α → φ` that evaluates\n`g` on each argument, then applies `f` to the results. Can be used, e.g., to transfer a relation\nfrom `β` to `α`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L19-L20","name":"Function.comp_left","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.comp_left","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L16-L17","name":"Function.comp_right","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Function.html#Function.comp_right","doc":""}]}